\begin_layout Section
\noindent
Why A Data Journalism Developer Studio?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Journalists today work in a world dominated by two trends:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Real-time many-to-many communications platforms
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Large sets of complex data with stories waiting to be told
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
There are hundreds of millions of Twitter accounts in most major nations
 of the world.
 Millions of those accounts are 
\emph on
active
\emph default
 Twitter users.
 Twitter and other networks exhibit complex patterns of interactions around
 people, places and events.
 And these intricate connection patterns change in real time.
 
\emph on
People break and discuss the news in real time on Twitter.

\emph default
 Journalists need at a minimum tools to collect Twitter data in real time,
 and better yet, tools to create databases of Twitter users and tweets and
 tools to analyze the databases.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
The other trend is what has been called an explosion of data:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Government data - national, regional, and local
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Business and financial data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Political fundraising, census/redistricting and vote tabulation data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Environmental, weather and climate data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Social network data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
And yes - traffic and sports data too
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
A journalist may find raw data in a spreadsheet, ready for analysis, but
 that's the best case.
 Or the data source may have built an API so the data can be queried by
 a developer.
 More often, though, data will have been massaged to tell the story favoring
 the data provider's point of view, formatted as a report in a PDF file,
 or even scanned from a printed document.
 And even access to the machine-readable data might require interaction
 with an authentication scheme.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
So computational journalists need tools to collect data, tools to interface
 with APIs if they've been provided, tools for extracting data from PDFs,
 tools for interacting with and scraping web sites, and tools for cleaning
 extracted data and massaging the variables and values into a format for
 analysis.
 Then, of course, come the tools for exploration and analysis of the data,
 data management, digital media creation and storytelling.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
\noindent
What Is The Data Journalism Developer Studio?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent

\emph on
Data Journalism Developer Studio 2012LX
\emph default
 is a collection of tools for computational journalists and developers.
 The tools are packaged as a
\emph on
 virtual appliance.

\emph default
 A virtual appliance is a collection of computer files, an image of the
 processor, memory and disk storage of a real computer.
 When hosted on a desktop or server virtualization platform, the appliance
 behaves like the computer it images.
 This has a number of benefits:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Since it is a collection of computer files, a virtual appliance can be stored
 on any storage medium anywhere when it is not in use.
 It requires a hosting platform only when it is in use.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
A virtual appliance can be transferred from one storage place to another
 over the Internet.
 In fact, some server virtualization platforms can do this while the appliance
 is running with no interruption to the users!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
The virtualization platform can save the state of the appliance using 
\emph on
snapshots
\emph default
.
 If an appliance becomes corrupted, it can be quickly restored to a known
 good condition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Adding more processors, RAM or disk storage to an appliance requires only
 changing some setting in the appliance, not purchase of new hardware.
 The hosting virtualization platform manages these resources.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
A virtual appliance can be deployed as either a server or a workstation.
\end_layout

