\begin_layout Section
\noindent
Why 100 Percent Open Source?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Open source software is robust
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
Open source software is low cost
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Although cost is certainly a consideration, the main reason for using 100
 percent open source software is robustness.
 The tools in Data Journalism Developer Studio 2012LX are proven technologies
 in wide use around the world.
 Open source software is crafted by highly-motivated self-regulated communities
 of experts.
 Security flaws, functionality defects and performance issues are rapidly
 found and fixed.
 And the peer review process yields software that is often more efficient
 than commercial counterparts
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Duplicating the functionality in Data Journalism Developer Studio 2012LX
 with commercial proprietary software would cost thousands of dollars in
 licenses.
 All the software in the appliance is freely downloadable without legal
 restrictions.
 The Data Journalism Developer Studio is 
\emph on
modular
\emph default
.
 The base appliance provides end-user tools for basic data collection and
 analysis and a browser-based desktop interface to cloud-based collaboration
 suites.
 Add-on installation scripts provide advanced tools for building desktop
 or server applications.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Add-on installation scripts provide end-user desktop and advanced specialized
 analysis tools building desktop or server applications
\end_layout

